public boolean compile(java.lang.String programName,
                       java.lang.String program,
                       java.lang.String buildPath,
                       boolean verbose)
                throws RunnerException
Compile with avr-gcc.

Parameters:
program - Sketch object to be compiled.
buildPath - Where the temporary files live and will be built from.
programName - the name of the combined sketch file w/ extension
Returns:
true if successful.
Throws:
RunnerException - Only if there's a problem. Only then.

message

public void message(java.lang.String s)
Part of the MessageConsumer interface, this is called whenever a piece (usually a line) of error message is spewed out from the compiler. The errors are parsed for their contents and line number, which is then reported back to Editor.

headerListFromIncludePath

public static java.lang.String[] headerListFromIncludePath(java.lang.String path)
Given a folder, return a list of the header files in that folder (but not the header files in its sub-folders, as those should be included from within the header files at the top-level).
